### Health check (no API key needed)
GET http://localhost:8080/health

###

### List users — no API key (should return 401)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/users

###

### List users — wrong API key (should return 401)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/users
X-API-Key: wrong-key

###

### List users — valid API key
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/users
X-API-Key: secret-key-123

###

### Get user by ID — valid API key
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/users/1
X-API-Key: secret-key-123

###

### Create user — valid API key
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: secret-key-123

{
  "name": "Ketaki",
  "email": "ketaki@example.com"
}

###

### Update user — valid API key
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/users/1
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: secret-key-123

{
  "name": "Akshad Updated",
  "email": "akshad.new@example.com"
}

###

### Delete user — valid API key
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/v1/users/2
X-API-Key: secret-key-123
